olive oil
1 packet Slow-Cooked Beef Brisket
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 carrot
1 bag super slaw
1 packet mayonnaise
1 drizzle sesame oil
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
20 g butter
1 drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Remove slow-cooked beef brisket from packet, then place in a baking dish (along with the packet juices!).
• Cover tightly with foil and bake for 12 minutes.
• Remove from oven, add sweet soy seasoning and sweet chilli sauce and turn to coat. Re-cover with foil and bake until heated through and liquid has slightly reduced, a further 12 minutes.

• Meanwhile, grate carrot.
• In a medium bowl, combine carrot, super slaw, mayonnaise and a drizzle of sesame oil and vinegar. Season to taste.
• Just before serving, microwave rice until steaming, 2-3 minutes. Stir the butter through the rice.

• Slice beef brisket.
• Divide butter rice between bowls. Top with sweet chilli-glazed brisket and creamy sesame slaw. Enjoy!